						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">But, due to the low-end hardware we have we end up having to represent the world with blocks, but a more realistic world nonetheless.</div>
<br />
<br />I for one enjoy older games due to their blocky world. To me it's not a limitation in recreating the "real" world, it <em>is</em> the basic structure of that world. The same goes for pixel art being seen as an approximation of how the characters really look; to me it is how the characters look. The somewhat abstract nature of the worlds is one of their appeals. I'll take Mario over a 3D game any day.</div>

